  "body": "# Problem\r\n\r\nThe most visible issue is the UX.\r\n\r\nreact-navigation implementation seems to be unnecessary complex and is undocumented. As a results, multiple wizards in the app have been implemented without using react-navigation and therefore navigation within them doesn't look and feel like the rest of the app, no gesture handling, no animated transitions. The current implementation also triggers some warning about deprecated usage of some elements of react-navigation.\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\n\r\n- upgrade to react-navigation 4\r\n- get rid of the cljs wrapper\r\n- get rid of legacy such as navigation stack in app-db\r\n- simplify the implementation\r\n- document the new implementation heavily\r\n\r\n## Acceptance Criteria\r\n\r\n- new documented implementation\r\n\r\n## Future Steps\r\n\r\n- Use react-navigation in the wizards that don't\r\n- Never accept a PR that doesn't use react-navigation",
